 Willowvale police and Mbashe Local Municipality officers arrested a 65-year-old man for possession of unlicensed firearm - a pistol with two rounds of ammunition. "The suspect was arrested on Wednesday, at about 13:45, at Lurhwayizo Village, in Willowvale," described police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The suspect will appear before the Willowvale Magistrate's Court on Thursday on charges of possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition." 